<reference id="itemgroup" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>itemgroup</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>itemgroup</xmlelement> element can be used to sub-divide or organize
  elements that occur inside a list item, definition, or parameter definition.</shortdesc>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm>itemgroup</indexterm><indexterm>specialization elements<indexterm>itemgroup</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section>The <xmlelement>itemgroup</xmlelement> element is particularly useful as a basis for
   specialization, where it can be used to group content within specialized list items or
   definitions. For example, in the OASIS task specialization, many elements within the
    <xmlelement>step</xmlelement> element are specialized from
   <xmlelement>itemgroup</xmlelement>.</section>
